The paper deals with privacy-preserving schemes for user requests, which is a topic that falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of a Markov chain to model user behavior suggests that information theory (cs.IT) may also be relevant. The optimization of download rates and the construction of privacy-preserving queries involve machine learning and optimization techniques, which are covered by the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of a window of future requests to construct privacy-preserving queries may also involve the use of statistical inference and probabilistic modeling, which are covered by the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
